The paper discusses a novel approach to conducting online exercises for teaching test-driven development (TDD) practices using Github workflows and continuous integration (CI) services. This falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and computer education (cs.EDU) categories. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of local code editors, testing frameworks, issue trackers, and CI services, which are relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and computer systems (cs.CE). Finally, the paper presents the results of participant surveys and teachers' observations, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) category.
